{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MutexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Take for example the following function:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","","    \/\/ now do a very complicated calculation to calculate the new","    \/\/ number, this might for example be a random number generator","    current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","","    return current_number;","  }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is easy to see that this won’t work in a multi-threaded"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"application. There current_number must be protected against shared"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"access. A ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used as a solution to this problem:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static GMutex mutex;","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","","    g_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Notice that the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is not initialised to any particular value."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Its placement in static storage ensures that it will be initialised"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to all-zeros, which is appropriate."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is placed in other contexts (eg: embedded in a struct)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then it must be explicitly initialised using ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_mutex_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" should only be accessed via g_mutex_ functions."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexRef","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"code":"GMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true},{"type":"text","tex